# Line-ending policy.
#
# perseus.py is a generated, single-file artifact run directly via its
# `#!/usr/bin/env python3` shebang. If it is checked out or built with CRLF
# endings (e.g. on Windows with core.autocrlf=true), the Linux kernel reads the
# shebang as `python3\r` and the entrypoint fails — this bites container and
# Iron Bank builds in particular. Pin it, and shell scripts (same shebang
# exposure), to LF regardless of a contributor's local git configuration.
perseus.py text eol=lf
*.sh text eol=lf
